I thought I would pass on this handy tip. A good way to clean your
carboy is to put some crushed ice inside, and add some salt. When you
start swooshing the ice around the carboy, the ice acts as an abrasive
and gets the hard to reach gunk off the sides.

Works great just make sure you rinse well.

Jim
