"A stitch in time saves nine."  No matter how busy you are, ALWAYS at
least fill the carboy up with water after you rack.  Now, what I also
try to do when I've finished racking, since I quite often am going to
use the yeast slurry and don't want it contaminated any more than
necessary, is to cover the top with either foil or a sandwich baggie and
a rubber band.  That will at least keep it from drying out and being
harder to clean later.

Re the comment about using too much cleaner (I use dish soap and
bleach), you can also do what I do to save time filling the carboy all
the way up; I fill it half way, drop a bucket over the top, flip them
over, and a half filled carboy has the top and neck immersed in cleaner.

Cheers.

Bill Velek
